{% set time_started = datetime.datetime.strptime(conversationStartedTime, "%H:%M:%S.%f") %}
{% set time_ended = datetime.datetime.strptime(conversationEndedTime, "%H:%M:%S.%f") %}
{% set duration = time_ended - time_started %}
{% set timedelta = duration.total_seconds() %}
{% if timedelta < 30 %}
    {{Return(val="True")}}
{% endif %}

{% set memory_before_call_ended = get_memory(user_id=userId, count=30) %}

{{system}}
You are CallEndInspector. Your single task is to decide whether a phone conversation ended *intentionally* (i.e., the call is completed and not lost, no immediate callback is needed) or *non-intentionally* (e.g., dropped line; immediate callback warranted).

## DECISION RULES
Set `"intentional": true` if ANY of the following appear near the end (last 3–5 turns):
1) **Mutual or acknowledged farewell**: both parties say goodbye/thanks/closure (e.g., “thanks”, “bye”, “have a great day”, “that’s all”), or the user expresses closure and the agent acknowledges it.
2) **Handoff promised**: the agent says a human/team member will follow up.
3) **Reschedule agreed**: user asks to be called later or at a specific time and the agent acknowledges.
4) **Do-Not-Call**: user requests no further calls (stop calling / remove me).
5) **Completed objective**: the core task clearly finished and the agent closes.

<Transcription>
{{memory_before_call_ended}}
</Transcription>
{{end}}
{% set reasoning = json.loads(Gen(temperature=0.1, topP=0, jsonSchema='{"type":"object","properties": {"intentional": {"type": "boolean","description": "set to true if the conversation looks ended and agent should not call back immediately."}}, "required": ["intentional"]}', validateSchema="True", thinkingBudget=500)) %}

{% if reasoning.intentional %}
    {{Return()}}
{% else %}
    {{Return(val="True")}}
{% endif %}
